    "Each decade thus brought its own innovations and breakthroughs that laid the foundation for the next generation of AI models 12.",
    "The year 2022 marked another turning point with the introduction of GPT-4 by OpenAI, a model developed by a team of 343 highly skilled scientists.",
    "These innovations were not limited to OpenAI; other significant models such as Bard and Gemini from Google 13, Claude from Anthropic 14 and others 15, developed by various organizations worldwide, also contributed to the landscape of generative AI.",
    "15 Mistral AI, \"Mixtral of Experts,\" December 11, 2023, https://mistral.ai/news/mixtral-of-experts/; Alyssa Hughes, \"Phi-2: The Surprising Power of Small Language Models,\" Microsoft Research (blog), December 12, 2023, https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/phi-2-the-surprising-power-of-small-language-models/; \"Llama 2,\" Meta AI, accessed January 14, 2024, https://ai.meta.com/llama-project.",
    "14 \"Introducing Claude,\" Anthropic, accessed January 14, 2024, https://www.anthropic.com/index/introducing-claude."
